   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Fighting Bullying in UK schools</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Diversity Role Models delivers workshops in schools to combat homophobia and other bullying. Workshops have been delivered to over 6,000 schoolchildren. Evaluation shows real attitude change in the children. A training package for staff ensures the positive messages are firmly embedded in the school culture. Currently working in the London area, DRM wants to expand its work to make our workshops available nationally. Funding will provide staff/volunteer training and fund a national conference.</narrative>
  </description>
